The paper deals with optimizing cloud configurations for workloads, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of Bayesian Optimization and low-level performance metrics suggests a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the need for an effective and reliable search method, which is relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of historical data to guide the search method suggests a connection to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and the use of machine learning techniques.
